snippet.textDisplay: How does it stack up to something like a 750Ti, though?... Because a Vega 11 (APU) pretty much sits between a 750 and 750Ti, I found, so... if the GT1010 is a joke compared to the 750(Ti), the Vega 11 is the easy choice. - For what?... Indeed "light gaming". Which, by the way, doesn't mean "bad/boring gaming", because you could run plenty of great games that are older or just less demanding. - (I just had a look at the specifications, and "on paper" the 750(Ti) is still "twice as good" as the GT1010, so... That thing basically gets beaten by an APU indeed. - The CPUs that have Vega 11 embedded might be a bit more expensive, but you then also have a very solid CPU, while saving space and probably power as well. - I just find that fascinating and impressive.)
